Package org.variantsync.diffdetective.variation.diff

Class Projection

java.lang.Object
org.variantsync.diffdetective.variation.tree.VariationNode<Projection>
org.variantsync.diffdetective.variation.diff.Projection
All Implemented Interfaces:
HasNodeType
public class Projection extends VariationNode<Projection>
A view of a DiffNode as variation node at a specific time.

See the project function in section 3.1 of our paper.

This class has to be instantiated using DiffNode.projection(org.variantsync.diffdetective.variation.diff.Time).

See Also:
  • DiffNode.projection(org.variantsync.diffdetective.variation.diff.Time)

    • getLabel

      public VariationNode.Label getLabel()
      Description copied from class: VariationNode
      Returns the label of this node.

      If HasNodeType.isArtifact() is true this may represent the source code of this artifact. Otherwise it may represent the preprocessor expression which was parsed to obtain VariationNode.getFormula(). In either case, this label may be an arbitrary value, selected according to the needs of the user of this class.

      Specified by:
      getLabel in class VariationNode<Projection>

    • getFormula

      public org.prop4j.Node getFormula()
      Description copied from class: VariationNode
      Returns the formula that is stored in this node. The formula is not null for mapping nodes with annotations and null otherwise (NodeType.ARTIFACT, NodeType.ELSE).

      If the type parameter T of this class is not a concrete variation tree, then the returned formula should be treated as unmodifiable to prevent undesired side effects (e.g., to DiffNodes).

      Specified by:
      getFormula in class VariationNode<Projection>

    • getID

      public int getID()
      Description copied from class: VariationNode
      Returns an integer that uniquely identifies this node within its tree.

      Some attributes may be recovered from this ID but this depends on the derived class. For example VariationTreeNode.fromID(int, java.util.List<java.lang.String>) can recover VariationNode.getNodeType() and the start line number. Beware that Projection returns DiffNode.getID() so this id is not fully compatible with VariationTreeNode.getID().

      Specified by:
      getID in class VariationNode<Projection>
